WEBVTT FILE

INTRO
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:20.000 line:10 position:50% align:middle size:100%
In the summer of 1948, the Soviets blocked all land and water routes to West Berlin.
The Western Allies’ response was to bring supplies to the city by air.
The Berlin Airlift lasted from 24th June 1948 until 12th May 1949. 
Horst Bert Molkenbuhr spent five years in a Nazi re-education camp as a child 
because his family was close to the left-wing Social Democratic Party. He tells us a story that is rarely mentioned in the usual reports about the airlift.
In 1949, thousands of teenagers spent their summer holidays on Tempelhof Field assisting the Allies.
He was one of them.

